Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,song.\NGive me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.55,0:01:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My head is a goal. I don't know. You\Nshould get warmed up with all this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.60,0:01:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,friction now. Everybody\Nshaking my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.88,0:01:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Wonderful to see you again.\N>> Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Not for great singing. Thank you. Good\Nhaving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.11,0:01:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah,\N>> I love those suspenders. Got them, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.75,0:01:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They are real.\NHi, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.15,0:01:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi.\N>> Oh my god. A little familiar face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.64,0:01:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning.\NAh,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> hello.\N>> Thank you for being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Morning, David. How are you?\N>> Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi.\NHey,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.31,0:02:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> everybody.\NOh, boy. We got to keep moving, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We got to keep moving, don't we?\N>> Did we get everybody here? No, we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.48,0:02:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't.\N>> Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello. Hello. Hello.\N>> How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.84,0:02:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You I do.\N>> I touched you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\N>> How you doing, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello.\N>> God bless you. God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How are you?\N>> Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi.\N>> Blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning.\N>> I missed you when you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.20,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. Did I miss anybody?\NDid I miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss anybody?\N>> I'll take another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.\N>> All right. Some people got two shakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.72,0:03:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> We're in for a treat today. We have a\Nsurprise for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.59,0:03:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What did you say?\NWe have a surprise for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.44,0:04:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.\NEvery day is a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.64,0:04:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to my age, waking up in the\Nmorning every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, baby. Here we go. Another day each.\NGot to hit that world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit it with your feet running. That's\Nthe way I keep doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit the feet with your feet running\Nto have an upbeat attitude towards life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.00,0:04:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Means letting go of all the negatives\Nand spiritual evolution which is what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.36,0:04:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,our courses are about. Uh anybody new\Nhere today? How many people are new? All
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,right. See we have the new and then we\Nhave people who have been to a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.88,0:04:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures.\NSo what we try to do is combine for the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,new people a quick rerun of the basics\Nand for the people who've been here a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,number of times uh stressing something\Nnew or looking at something that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with but from a a new\Nviewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Ntoday we're talking about spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,traps. I don't know what that means, but\Nit says that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote trips and they misspelled it.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.47,0:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,trips, traps, troops.\NWe'll have spiritual troops here later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.24,0:05:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start with the spiritual trips and\Nthen we'll hit the traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.80,0:05:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Trip trap troops. So, there we'll cover\Nit all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.36,0:05:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. Never take life too seriously.\NOne of the traps is taking life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.75,0:05:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely seriously. You see, without a\Nsense of humor, you don't survive too
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:06:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,well.\NThere's different styles of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.44,0:06:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,expression, spiritual teaching.\NUh each one fits its own niche
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and fits different moods. Fits different\Nmoods. I like humor as a teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.60,0:06:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,technique, as a modality. And I like\Nhumor as a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we always start as we said with\Nthe end of the lectures. We start at the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,end and work back to the beginning. Most\Npeople start at the beginning and work
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.47,0:06:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the end. But by the time you get to\Nthe end, you forgotten what the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning was. So we'll start with the\Nend, which is the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.24,0:06:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get that in the beginning, you\Ncan take a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.03,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as somebody points it out to\Nyou, what I'm going to say is extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,simple and obvious. You see to start out\Nwith the overall context
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that creation and evolution are one in\Nthe same thing that sets an overall
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.84,0:07:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,context.\NEvolution is nothing but the process of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.03,0:07:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,creation.\NCreation is evolution and evolution is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.47,0:07:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,creation. So that ends that argument.\NThe way to see that is you have to jump
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.08,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of cause and\Neffect. The dualistic conceptualization
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of cause and effect because the thing\Noccurs prior to something else. We
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,presume it's the cause.\NAnd there's a Latin phrase that points
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,out the fallacy of that which I've\Nforgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Post hawk ergoctor hawk.\NEverybody got that? Post hawk erggo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.08,0:08:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hawk. Because a thing follows a thing\Ndoesn't mean it's caused by that which
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,precedes it. Because there is nothing\Nthat does precede it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that precedes it is\Nyou're witnessing. The phenomena there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.44,0:08:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is no sequential sequences is in the\Nwitness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.28,0:08:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The way things come about is\Npotentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when conditions are favorable.\NBut you're not seeing causality. What
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.91,0:08:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're seeing is emergence.\NThe potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.48,0:08:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\Ncaterpillar, the little thing in the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cocoon, the crystallis,\Nit doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.92,0:09:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,cause the moth of the butterfly. See, it\Nemerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.39,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It has that potential. That potential\Nthen actualizes as a butterfly if
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions are appropriate\Nbut not because it's caused. Nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,causes nothing causes it to do that. The\Nconditions are there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate heat, humidity, time of\Nyear, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what you see is the emergence of\Npotentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,appearing in actuality.\NThe fact that you think it appears there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.36,0:09:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it is there. It's just\Nthat in your mind you think one thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.83,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,occurring before the other and one thing\Nis causing another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the reason we stress that is because\Nthe Newtonian paradigm the the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.72,0:09:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of the 400s\Nuh is the great stopper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people get beyond consciousness\Nlevel 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, not too many people get to the 400s\Nif you ask me, but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking this anyway. So the the\Nintellect and the mind is the world of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.04,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the 400s. That's the word of world of\Nscience and mathematics and aeronautics,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,engineering.\NIt's a world of great benefit to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.48,0:10:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. The 400s pharmaceuticals\Nuh and the relief of the suffering of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.83,0:10:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind that comes out of the 400s is\Nincredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Seldom seldom however does the mind jump\Nthe Newtonian paradigm of cause and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.07,0:10:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,effect and calibrate in the 500s. So at\N499 we have the greatest geniuses of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.48,0:10:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,history. We have Freud, we have Sir\NIsaac Newton, we have Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the great intellects.\NUh so genius is usually around 4 480 to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.32,0:11:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,499. Huh?\NBut then at consciousness level 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a paradigm jump from out there,\Nfrom the illusion of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of subjectivity.\NIt's the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning we planned an experiential\Nkind of a lesson. See it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential.\NThe experiential cannot be proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.76,0:11:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot be proven.\NYou know and there was recently a blog
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.76,0:11:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,site they criticized kinesiology from\Nthe viewpoint of the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.68,0:11:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of causality etc. You know, anyway, what\Nthe person misses, the critic thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that the only things that are real are\Nthings that within the 400s, things that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.12,0:11:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can prove.\NAnd therefore, anything beyond 499 is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.04,0:11:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,unreal, though.\NOn the other hand, he doesn't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:12:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NIt sounds sort of saucy and provocative,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.88,0:12:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but\Nhe doesn't believe it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because where do we live? Even if we\Nhold to the Newtonian paradigm, we only
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.20,0:12:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hold to it because subjectively to us it\Nis truth. To us it is truth. So
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore all people live by faith.\NI got a kick out of the skeptic because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he ridicules faith and he writes from\Ncomplete and 101% absolute faith in his
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,own mentalization about it all.\NYou don't live in the tinian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.48,0:12:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk about it. You deal with it as\Nan out there. You see, but you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,live there. Where you live is in\Nsubjectivity, the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.27,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in the radiance of\Nconsciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.76,0:12:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the e fllororesence of\Nconsciousness experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.68,0:13:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you live. And the quality\Nof that subjective experiential reality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is what a more mature person is\Nconcerned about. Therefore, love becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of a greater value than possessions.\NUm, depending on the possession of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.76,0:13:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,course\Nbecause some people love their
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,possessions. They love their\Npossessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he say? For my cold cold hand,\Nyou will pull the rifle or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Love their possessions. Yeah. All right.\NSo that's the first trap we come across
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is to reject the source of your\Nhappiness outside of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.20,0:13:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fatal.\NThe minute you project the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness is out something outside of\Nyourself, you now are victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The catastrophe hasn't have happened\Nyet, but it's inevitable. Yeah. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if your happiness is dependent on an\Nexternal over which you have no control,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a world of transition. Nothing\Nremains the same. Nothing remains the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,same.\NNothing remains the same. It's a world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of constant evolutionary change.\Nbiologically evolutionary. Evolution is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly changing.\NThat which you think is eternal slowly
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.19,0:14:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,turns to rust and dissolves. You see,\Nand when you visit places like Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.39,0:14:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where, you know,\Nsome 12,000 years of prior history, uh
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to get a feeling for what age\Nis, what age is, you see. So if you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,attach your happiness then or your\Nsurvival to something that is out there
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.56,0:14:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,uh now it's only a matter of time\Nthat out thereess can also be a mental
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.95,0:15:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,position a positionality in which you\Nbecome enamored.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.51,0:15:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We get emails\Nall the time from people that are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.83,0:15:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,enamored of some concept and something\Nin some book doesn't agree with that uh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,point of view. You know, and you can see\Nlike the child in them is just enamored
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of this concept. You know, usually we\Nget whales and dolphins at least a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.83,0:15:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,couple times a month.\Nlike dolphins are going to get them to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven. Is it Jesus Christ going to be\Nyour savior or a dolphin? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You gota make\NI don't know why whales and dolphins
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate what they do. We got an expert\Nhere with us today. Maybe she'll explain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.95,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to us. She already did explain to me,\Nbut I forgot what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh because something calibrates below\N200 doesn't mean that it's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.63,0:16:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that I wouldn't consult\Nthem uh in their office about an
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,amputation or something.\NYou really don't want a brain surgeon
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates below 200.\NBut you know, most pets, our birds and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.19,0:16:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that, all the things we love\Nand we adore below 200. Doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.80,0:16:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not lovable and that it isn't\Nof any intrinsic value.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.51,0:16:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just it means that you wouldn't\Nconsult them about your legal affairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NSo if we see that the world is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.27,0:16:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,transitory and\Nthat the process going on is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution,\Nevolution then is the way we witness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,creation.\NThe way we witness creation is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.68,0:16:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary unfolding of potentiality\Nbecoming an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.07,0:17:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which we then sequentially witness and\Nproject the concept of time to an out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.19,0:17:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NWell, that'll get get you a PhD right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.16,0:17:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Just write that up for your\Nprofessor. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.64,0:17:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it means, but it sure\Nsounds impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that that's what happens as you\Nlet go identifying without theirness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with positionalities\Nthen you withdraw into witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.28,0:17:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you become your life becomes\Nwitnessing
