Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.72,0:58:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the downside of the human\Nmind that without help from usually
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.40,0:58:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,external\Nit's not possible to arrive at the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.92,0:59:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by oneself. Therefore,\Nthe great religion, the great avatars
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.24,0:59:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nrepresented the energy field without
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.72,0:59:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which mankind would not be able to grasp\Nits own reality. Without that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.72,0:59:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,field of the avatar, radiating down\Nthrough the centuries for a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.11,0:59:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,years, uh there's no the human mind has\Nno capacity to realize the truth of its
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.83,0:59:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,own existence, much less the origin of\Nits own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.68,0:59:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,human mind is incapable of it. So that\Nwas the function. Then the great
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.44,0:59:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual figures of history\Ncontextualize reality from an overall
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.35,0:59:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,greater context than human experience.\NMany countries then you see Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.88,0:59:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,especially many many\Num were theocracies for some
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.28,0:59:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,generations. They were out of religion\Nwas formed the structure of the society,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.11,1:00:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,its laws, its courts, its orderliness,\Nmorals and ethics etc. And then some of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.55,1:00:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,course later became secular didn't want\Nto acknowledge the the source but the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.31,1:00:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,source of secular countries is 100%\Nreligious. All secular sec secular
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.96,1:00:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,countries in Europe\Noriginated from a theological position.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.20,1:00:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Right and wrong, responsibility,\Naccountability, guilt versus innocence,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.24,1:00:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic tenants of civilization and\Nsociety arose out of theological
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.68,1:00:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts. Yeah. Mhm. And then later on\Nyou can refute them and say we don't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.31,1:00:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,want any theology and we don't want any\Nreligion and we don't want God anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.28,1:00:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The ACLU sent me a solicitation the\Nother day and and I was going to put a
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.55,1:00:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,$100 bill in there until I noticed on\N$100 bill it said in God we trust. So I
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.64,1:00:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't want to offend them. So I put it\Nback in my pocket and spend it on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.96,1:01:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,foolishness.\NOh God
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.11,1:01:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in God we trust. Yeah, see the\Nconstitution says let let the congress
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.04,1:01:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not establish any religion\Nnor prohibit the practice thereof
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.64,1:01:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,nor prohibit the practice thereof. And\Nyou notice how the secularists always
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.83,1:01:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,give you the first part.\NNever do they give you the second part.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.11,1:01:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether putting up a Christmas tree is\Nestablishing a religion, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.55,1:01:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But it certainly is\Nuh enjoying the practice the row you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.52,1:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know you see so then is so selective so\Nyou can see a positionalized mind
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.40,1:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't like the second half of the uh\Nsentence so it just ignores it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.07,1:02:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you the warp the half half the\Ntruth warp you know
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.59,1:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not say and nowhere does it say\Nseparation of church or state nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.00,1:02:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it say separation or church\Nor state? Those three words do not even
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.40,1:02:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,appear. So all the endless quoting of\Ncertain things
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.52,1:02:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are the traps that we fall into. Those\Nare the traps of memes. Meme and and a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.28,1:02:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,meme is a saying which is spoken so\Noften that everybody begins to assume
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.35,1:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's truth. Everybody thinks the\Nconstitution says separation of church
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.44,1:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and state. How many people here believe\Nthat?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.00,1:02:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest of you are lying. Uh\Nbefore I said that, how many people
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.11,1:02:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,would say all right\Nseparation of church and state was the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.92,1:02:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,con was an interpretation a judicial\Ninterpretation
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.83,1:02:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the and if you don't believe me look at\Nit because I looked over there is no
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.88,1:03:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,words separation or church or state\Nthose three words do not appear none of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.24,1:03:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,them in the constitution to let the\Ncongress not establish a religion nor
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.64,1:03:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,prohibit the free practice thereof.\NSo another trap then is we get
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.07,1:03:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,brainwashed without knowing it. You\Nrepeat separation of church and state
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.07,1:03:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over again. Probably after\Nabout a while everybody thinks that's
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.59,1:03:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what the constitution says.\NHow many people run into their library,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.24,1:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pull out the big book and reread the\Nconstitution to see what the hell it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.00,1:03:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,says? I did. You know I did. I did.\Nmeticulously. In fact, I clipped it out
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.16,1:03:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it on my bullet board. This is\Nwhat the Constitution says.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.35,1:03:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Few of us left in the world that know\Nwhat the Constitution actually says.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.68,1:03:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the media have so\Nbrainwashed us that even
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.55,1:04:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous people, integrous people uh\Nare programmed to believe that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.76,1:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,facious. Mhm.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.92,1:04:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the biggest traps in is our\Nnaivete.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.28,1:04:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our naivee. What time do we have to\Nstop?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.72,1:04:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 11.\N>> Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.16,1:04:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 11:15.\N>> Okay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.16,1:04:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to check with the timekeeper.\NWhat ending are we?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.55,1:04:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hit go to the subjective, when\Nyou go to the experiential, you sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.88,1:04:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,lose track of time. you because you're\Ndealing in timelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.55,1:04:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego superimposes\Ntime. It put like tra puts it on the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.72,1:04:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of the uh the tape as it's going\Nby. It puts a time track on experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.03,1:04:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a projection of the ego\Nwithin the experiential world itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.96,1:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing. That's a\Nconcept, a Newtonian concept, an
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.00,1:05:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,extraction. We superimpose a measurement\Ncalled time and then project it as
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.79,1:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,though time exists out there. And as\Nlong as we stay within that paradigm, it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.24,1:05:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,works. E= MC² works. It works so long as\Nyou stay within that paradigm. But once
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.55,1:05:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you get outside of that paradigm, uh\Nit's meaningless. Meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.24,1:05:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to tolerate the world and\Nstay in a position of goodwill
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.44,1:05:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if you see its evolutionary nature. The\Nphenomenal world is constantly changing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.64,1:05:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that it's con constantly\Nemerging. The potentiality of this arm
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.48,1:05:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to rise in the air uh does so because\Nthat's the actualization of that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.24,1:05:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality.\NAnd if a certain thought should occur in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.44,1:06:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, then the hand will do what it\Ndid. But it's doing that autonomously.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.03,1:06:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no cause for the hand to do\Nthat. You say, well, it was the thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.72,1:06:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but there was no cause for the\Nthought. The thought was also
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.48,1:06:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous. Therefore, the next\Nrealization is that everything is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.31,1:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,happening of its own.\NNothing is being caused by anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.92,1:06:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is autonomous, spontaneous\Nand unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.28,1:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is expressing the essence of\Nthat which it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.88,1:06:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not as a cause and effect, but as an\Nautomatic spontaneous consequence of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.76,1:06:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it is.\NThe ego likes to take credit. Oh, I
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.96,1:06:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thought of that.\NThe ego did not think of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.83,1:06:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All that occurs is occurring\Nautonomously and spontaneously. There is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.83,1:06:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no cause.\NHow about being deliberate and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.92,1:06:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, I can be deliberately." Yeah, but\Nyou're being spontaneously deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.83,1:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You are being autonomously spontaneously\Ndeliberate.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.28,1:07:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, I'd have to say, "I'm going\Nto be spontaneous and I'm going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.83,1:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous about being spontaneous."\NBut that was deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.00,1:07:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But deliberation was spontaneously.\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.76,1:07:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to get you behind the scenery\Nso that you see, you know, like the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.24,1:07:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wizard of Oz.\NDon't pay any attention to me back here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.83,1:07:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the Wizard of Oz. Don't pay any\Nattention to me back here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.79,1:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is actually autonomously\Nhappening as a consequence of that which
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.28,1:07:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it is. Simultaneously\Nthat which it is is what it means.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.03,1:07:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing is and its meaning are one\Nin the same thing. You see to try and
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.64,1:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,define it, you've already got a duality\Nof this meaning of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.88,1:08:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing means is what it is.\NWhat does the sound of the bag pipe
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.79,1:08:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? I can tell you what it recalls.\NWhat it reverberates well with.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.72,1:08:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It means what it is.\NThat sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.52,1:08:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last sound a warrior wanted\Nto hear was the sound of bag pipes
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.27,1:08:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,coming over the hill.\NThe last sound you want to hear on the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.35,1:08:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,battlefield is the sound of bag pipes of\Nthe enemy coming towards you
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.52,1:08:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know this is death.\NThis is death. You're going to live or
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.71,1:08:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,die. There's an absolute sound to it. An\Nabsoluteness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.71,1:08:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,without which the heart of mankind we\Nwould none of would have none of us
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.83,1:08:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,would have survived\Nwithout that valor and that courage
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.60,1:09:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is inherent. Most people don't\Neven acknowledge it in themsel. Do you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.67,1:09:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,realize what it takes to be a human\Nbeing to walk around with your head up
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.88,1:09:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world of assistitudes from\Nmoment to moment? Within any second you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.04,1:09:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can be snuffed out.\NYou can start off the day with a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.79,1:09:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,headache\Nand then it gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.67,1:09:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now to just survive the cicissitudes of\Ntiredness of sickness and death and the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.71,1:09:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,fact that everything everything that\Nthat you value eventually disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.79,1:09:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that you hang on to sooner or\Nlater goes away. And therefore how to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.31,1:09:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,live in the world without suffering pain\Nof loss and frustration and desire
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.40,1:09:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is the contentness. Contentness with the\Nsubjectivity of that which you are in
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.35,1:09:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the immediate moment.\NEverything as it is as it is. And with
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.88,1:09:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total acceptance. It can be\Nthat way all the time. All the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.96,1:10:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When they're about to be head your take\Nyour head off. You say to the headsman,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.64,1:10:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"Listen, don't feel bad about it. It's\Nyour job. You know what I mean? That's
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.56,1:10:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what I tell him. Listen, don't worry,\Nman. Just do your thing. You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.28,1:10:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, somebody's got to be the\Nhusband, you know what I mean? He's got
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.15,1:10:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a wife, kids to feed. You know what I\Nmean? Or he gets so much ahead, you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.60,1:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,know?\NMy head is his supper. You know what I
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.84,1:10:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,mean?\NIn that way, you can al almost transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.19,1:10:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,physical pain. Of course, I've explained\Nto you how I've done it and had surgery
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.08,1:10:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,without anesthesia.\NAnd that's by taking no positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.64,1:10:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nabsolutely not resisting the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.88,1:10:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 of a second. The minute you\Nresist the pain, it's it's excruciating.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.60,1:10:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you surrender to it, then\Nit's like you're lifted out of it. And
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.71,1:11:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as the surgery went on, I was lifted\Ninto a beatotific space. I was sorry
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.00,1:11:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was over.\NIsn't there something else you got to
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.80,1:11:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,snip or cut?\NConstantly surrendering actually allows
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.76,1:11:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you to go into an infinite timeless\Nspace of exquisite joy and peace. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.80,1:11:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,like the angelic forces lift you out of\Nyour body and you witness the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.76,1:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality but you're not subject to\Nthe physicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.48,1:11:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Beatotific state. So those are also\Navailable to us. the beatotific states
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.84,1:11:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind has experienced\Nand the sound of the heart and the bag
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.64,1:11:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pipes also gives us a vision of that\Nalso a vision
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.71,1:11:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which is somewhat represented by\Nreligion in a certain way there's a
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.15,1:12:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,certain semiilitary\Num mystique about religion also
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.19,1:12:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the heart of the warrior the\Nbreastplate
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.56,1:12:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh etc are symbolic ic spiritual\Nand ethical principles
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.36,1:12:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by which man stands. You see, man stands\Nand civilization stands by certain of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.80,1:12:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,these principles.\NSo that's what I thought we should
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.71,1:12:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experience together. I wanted us to do\Nit together. Experience the heart of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.96,1:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind, the heart of the child, the\Nvalor that goes beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.80,1:12:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, that sound is that energy and if you\Ncling to it, it will take you through
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.08,1:12:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. I've gone through anything\Nwith that energy within myself. And as
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.88,1:12:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan has told me,\Nthrough the fear and the agony and the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.76,1:12:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,pain of childbirth,\Nthe heart of all the women who have
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.67,1:13:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,faced it, lived it, survived it and died\Nin the midst of it, bled to death or
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.12,1:13:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,died if child had fever. The valor then\Nthe courage of the human being
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.92,1:13:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh is what we salute today. And uh\Nso I thought together we could salute
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.88,1:13:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the heart of man kind.\N>> Huh? Let's all salute the man kind
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.40,1:13:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. God bless us all. Amen. We'll\Ntake a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.84,1:13:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I on? Yes.\NWell, here we we reassembled.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.23,1:13:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the lecture came to an end\Nwas because I couldn't really talk
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.04,1:13:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore.\NHow many people here cried or felt like
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.23,1:14:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,crying? Isn't that amazing?\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.04,1:14:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. And we touch the core of the\Nheart. Yeah. That's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.67,1:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's hard to keep talking after\Nthat. So we limp through it at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.15,1:14:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay. So now about a third of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.64,1:14:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,knew and therefore we run through the\Nbasics again. uh because every time you
